cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of metric embeddings, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of geometric topology in the proof suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The inapproximability results are based on reductions, which is a common technique in complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the use of random projection and the analysis of distortion suggest a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
